    <tags>bff-api, ai, models</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>BFF code implementation; produces the canonical Tool Registry data contract consumed by every Phase 2 task and downstream Phase 3/4 work; ADR-013 facade boundary; tags include bff-api + ai</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Foundation model for tasks 021–026; its output (types, JSON contract) must exist before any sibling can compile. Single critical-path task within Phase 2.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build the `ToolRegistry` extended-metadata data model (POCOs + JSON serialization) inside `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/ToolRegistry/`. This model is the canonical contract for Tool Registry entries in BFF code, mirrors the `sprk_toolregistry` Dataverse entity created in task 011, and is the input shape for the `spaarke-resource-registry-index` indexer (task 016). It MUST include all 11 extended-metadata fields enumerated in spec.md FR-07 and design.md §5 (Classification, CostClass, LatencyClass, Idempotency, AuthMode, Discoverability, ModelTier, PhaseRestrictions, EvidenceRequired, IsAlwaysOnInAssistant, PromoteInContexts).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET 8 / C# engineer with deep familiarity with the Spaarke BFF AI feature module conventions (`Services/Ai/`), strongly-typed serialization (`System.Text.Json` with source generators where applicable), and ADR-013 facade boundary discipline.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three concrete outcomes:
    1. **POCO data model** — `ToolRegistryEntry`, plus enum/value types for `Classification`, `CostClass`, `LatencyClass`, `Idempotency`, `AuthMode`, `ModelTier`, and complex types for `Discoverability` (with `SemanticDescription`, `Aliases`, `SampleInvocations`) and `PhaseRestrictions` (per-phase deny-tools).
    2. **JSON serialization contract** — round-trip stable JSON shape used by (a) Dataverse → BFF reads, (b) AI Search index push, (c) `ToolRegistryEndpoints.cs` (task 021) response payloads. JsonSerializerOptions registered via `AddActionEngineModule()`.
    3. **Unit tests** — round-trip serialization, defaulting behavior (missing fields default sensibly), and validation (e.g., `PhaseRestrictions` cannot contain a phase the parent Action does not declare).

    Deliverable: `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/ToolRegistry/ToolRegistryModel.cs` + `ToolRegistryEnums.cs` + `Discoverability.cs` + `PhaseRestriction.cs`; unit tests at `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/ToolRegistry/`.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Spec.md FR-07 enumerates the 11 extended-metadata fields. Design.md §5 documents the semantic intent of each. The joint signal-envelope coordination with the Insights Engine project means the field shapes (especially `Classification` and `Discoverability`) MUST stay aligned with what `coordination-assessment-with-insights-engine.md` §4.8 declares.

      The model is consumed in three places:
      - `ToolRegistryEndpoints.cs` (task 021) for CRUD + query
      - `FindResourcesTool.cs` (task 022) for semantic-search response shaping
      - The AI Search index push pipeline (task 016 — index already created; this task may need to coordinate field mapping)

      This task is the data-foundation task within Phase 2. All sibling tasks (021–026) depend on its output. It produces NO endpoints, NO services with side effects — only types + serialization + tests.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/ToolRegistry/ToolRegistryModel.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/ToolRegistry/ToolRegistryEnums.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/ToolRegistry/Discoverability.cs</file>
