    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">.NET 8 Minimal API. POCOs only — NO EF Core entity bleed into the model. Strongly typed; nullable reference types respected.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Endpoint-filter auth applies at task 021 (endpoints). This task is data-only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism. JsonSerializerOptions registration via `AddActionEngineModule()` extension. Do NOT register loose `IOptions&lt;&gt;` in `Program.cs`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">PublicContracts/ facade boundary. If any type here is referenced by CRUD-side callers, it MUST be exposed via the facade — not directly. This task's model types live under `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/ToolRegistry/` and are internal to AE.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Tool dispatch audit (Tier 2 + Tier 3) will hash these structures. JSON round-trip MUST be deterministic (e.g., property ordering controlled) to keep hashes stable.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">N/A here (no endpoints).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Publish-size: avoid Newtonsoft.Json unless already transitively present. Prefer `System.Text.Json`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge checklist binding: placement decision (in BFF, internal to `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/`), no new CRUD→AI dependencies, no new NuGet packages without justification.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">11 extended-metadata fields from spec.md FR-07 MUST all be present: Classification, CostClass, LatencyClass, Idempotency, AuthMode, Discoverability, ModelTier, PhaseRestrictions, EvidenceRequired, IsAlwaysOnInAssistant, PromoteInContexts.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Classification and Discoverability shapes coordinate with Insights Engine per coordination-assessment-with-insights-engine.md §4.8; do NOT diverge.</constraint>
  </constraints>

