  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm working tree clean, baseline build passes, branch is `work/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`. (task-execute Step 0)</step>
    <step order="1">Read all files in `&lt;knowledge&gt;&lt;files&gt;`. Pay close attention to spec.md FR-07, design.md §5 (Tool Registry metadata section), coordination-assessment §4.8 (joint Classification + Discoverability shapes), and bff-extensions.md (binding governance).</step>
    <step order="2">Sketch the type hierarchy on paper / in a scratch note: `ToolRegistryEntry` (root) → 11 metadata fields. Identify which become enums (`Classification`, `CostClass`, `LatencyClass`, `Idempotency`, `AuthMode`, `ModelTier`) and which are complex types (`Discoverability`, `PhaseRestrictions`). Document defaulting rules (e.g., `IsAlwaysOnInAssistant` defaults to false; `PromoteInContexts` defaults to empty array).</step>
    <step order="3">Implement enums in `ToolRegistryEnums.cs`. Use `[JsonStringEnumConverter]` for stable JSON shape. Document each enum value with XML comments referencing design.md §5.</step>
    <step order="4">Implement `Discoverability.cs` (SemanticDescription, Aliases[], SampleInvocations[]) and `PhaseRestriction.cs` (per-phase deny-tools structure). These are the two complex value types.</step>
    <step order="5">Implement `ToolRegistryModel.cs` containing `ToolRegistryEntry`. All 11 extended-metadata fields present + ToolId, DisplayName, Description, ParameterSchema (JSON schema as string or `JsonElement`). Use nullable reference types; record types where appropriate for value semantics.</step>
    <step order="6">Configure JSON serialization: explicit `JsonSerializerOptions` in `AddActionEngineModule()` extension (DI). PropertyNamingPolicy = camelCase. Enums via string converter. Property ordering stable (so audit hashes from ADR-015 are deterministic — alphabetic property names within each level OR source-generator default ordering).</step>
    <step order="7">Write unit tests at `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/ToolRegistry/ToolRegistryModelTests.cs`: (a) round-trip serialization for a fully populated entry, (b) round-trip for minimal entry (defaults apply), (c) enum string-shape stability, (d) PhaseRestrictions validation (deny-tool references valid phase names), (e) JSON shape locked to a golden fixture (regression guard against accidental shape drift).</step>
    <step order="8">Verify build + test passes: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` and `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`. Run `dotnet format` to keep style consistent.</step>
    <step order="9">Verify NFR-10 publish-size impact is zero (no new NuGet packages added). Run `dotnet list package src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ --include-transitive` before/after if uncertain.</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates: `code-review` on the new files; `adr-check` to verify ADR-013 (facade boundary respected — model is internal to AE folder), ADR-010 (DI registration only via module extension), ADR-029 (no new NuGet packages).</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 020 ✅. Update `current-task.md`: task 020 complete; next: Phase 2 Group C parallel (tasks 022, 023, 024) + tasks 021, 025, 026 in parallel.</step>
    <step order="11">Document any deviations or design notes in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/`. Commit with a brief recap message.</step>
  </steps>

