  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`ToolRegistryEntry` exists with all 11 extended-metadata fields enumerated in spec.md FR-07 (Classification, CostClass, LatencyClass, Idempotency, AuthMode, Discoverability, ModelTier, PhaseRestrictions, EvidenceRequired, IsAlwaysOnInAssistant, PromoteInContexts).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Round-trip JSON serialization unit test passes for a fully populated entry and for a minimally populated entry (defaults apply correctly).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Enum JSON shape uses string converter (verified by golden-fixture unit test); ordering is stable for ADR-015 audit hashing.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`Classification` + `Discoverability` shapes match the coordination-assessment-with-insights-engine.md §4.8 contract (verified by inspection in code review).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Build passes: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` exits 0. Tests pass: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` exits 0.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No new NuGet packages added (NFR-10 publish-size preserved). Verified by `git diff src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Sprk.Bff.Api.csproj`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Model types live under `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/ToolRegistry/` and are NOT exposed via `PublicContracts/` (ADR-013 boundary — verified by grep).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Supports spec gate G2 (meta-tools discovery flow) by providing the canonical contract `FindResources` / `GetResourceDetail` / `InvokeResource` consume.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Coordination with Insights Engine on `Classification` + `Discoverability` shapes is non-negotiable. If a shape conflict is detected during this task, escalate before committing — do NOT diverge silently. The signal envelope contract is jointly owned per `coordination-assessment-with-insights-engine.md` §4.8.

    The 11 fields enumeration is the most important checklist for this task. Missing one breaks downstream tasks (notably 022 `FindResources` which surfaces `Discoverability.SemanticDescription`, and 026 phase deny-tools which consume `PhaseRestrictions`).

    Audit hash stability (ADR-015) demands deterministic property ordering. Lean on `System.Text.Json` source generators or explicit `[JsonPropertyOrder]` to lock the shape.
  </notes>

